---
title: Zucchini and Asparagus Farro Bowl with Parmesan and Lemon
description: Fun fact about farro: the grain has roots from ancient times when it was used by the early Egyptians. Today, it’s a popular Italian staple that has attracted the attention of chefs around the world for its dense, chewy texture and nutty flavor. We made it into a risotto-style dish with Parmesan, veggies, a kick of citrus flavor, and a sprinkle of walnuts.
